cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on collaborative spectrum sensing in IoT networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm utilizes an online learning framework, which is a common technique in the field of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The use of normalized weights as a proxy metric of detection accuracy is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the issue of inter-user collision and misdetection, which are security concerns in wireless networks. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed strategy to extend the field life of devices without compromising on detection accuracy involves control of the sensing behavior of devices.
